en_9164684_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – Former DIG Prasanna Nanayakkara, who is under arrest on charges of concealing evidence in the murder of journalist Lasantha Wickrematunge, was further remanded until May 14.
en_9164684_1	The order was issued when the case was taken up before Mount Lavinia Chief Magistrate Mohammed Mihail, today (May 1).
en_9164684_2	The Former DIG’s attorney presented facts to court on April 23 requesting for bail to be granted to his client, and a verdict in this regard was to be delivered today (May 1).
en_9164684_3	Senior State Counsel Janaka Bandara presented facts against the bail request for Former DIG Prasanna Nanayakkara.
en_9164684_4	President’s Counsel Anura Medagama, appearing on behalf of Former DIG Prasanna Nanayakkara, requested time to respond to the facts presented by the Senior State Counsel.
en_9164684_5	Thereby, with the consent of both parties, the hearing was postponed to May 14.
en_9164684_6	Another suspect in custody over the case, Inspector Thissa Sugathapala, was also further remanded until May 14.
